#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.194"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.194:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.194:0.2"
msgid "20. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "20. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.194:0.3"
msgid "194. Kāraṇapālīsutta"
msgstr "194. With Kāraṇapālī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.237"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

#. VAR: kāraṇapālī → karaṇapālī (mr)
msgctxt "an5.194:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo licchavīnaṃ kammantaṃ kāreti."
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin Kāraṇapālī was working for the Licchavis."

msgctxt "an5.194:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;"
msgstr "He saw the brahmin Piṅgiyānī coming off in the distance"

msgctxt "an5.194:1.4"
msgid "disvā piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:2.1"
msgid "“Handa kuto nu bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī āgacchati divā divassā”ti?"
msgstr "“So, Piṅgiyānī, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.2"
msgid "“Itohaṃ, bho, āgacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa santikā”ti."
msgstr "“I’m coming, my good man, from the presence of the ascetic Gotama.”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Taṃ kiṃ maññati bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ? "
"Paṇḍito maññe”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What do you think of the ascetic Gotama’s proficiency in wisdom? Do you "
"think he’s astute?”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.4"
msgid "“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jānissāmi."
msgstr ""
"“My good man, who am I to judge the ascetic Gotama’s proficiency in wisdom?"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.5"
msgid ""
"Sopi nūnassa tādisova yo samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jāneyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"You’d really have to be on the same level to judge his proficiency in "
"wisdom.”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.6"
msgid "“Uḷārāya khalu bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsāya pasaṃsatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Master Piṅgiyānī praises the ascetic Gotama with magnificent praise indeed.”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.7"
msgid "“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsissāmi."
msgstr "“Who am I to praise the ascetic Gotama?"

#. VAR: Pasatthappasatthova → pasaṭṭhapasaṭṭho ca (s1-3, km, mr) | pasatthapasatho va (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.194:2.8"
msgid "Pasatthappasatthova so bhavaṃ gotamo seṭṭho devamanussānan”ti."
msgstr "He is praised by the praised as the best of gods and humans.”"

msgctxt "an5.194:2.9"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī atthavasaṃ sampassamāno samaṇe gotame evaṃ "
"abhippasanno”ti?"
msgstr "“But for what reason are you so devoted to the ascetic Gotama?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso aggarasaparititto na aññesaṃ hīnānaṃ rasānaṃ piheti;"
msgstr ""
"“Suppose a person was completely satisfied by the best tasting food. They "
"wouldn’t be attracted to anything that tasted inferior."

msgctxt "an5.194:3.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—"
msgstr "In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—"

# BB notes this occurrence of the 4 angas, and mentions two possible explanations. He omits a third possibility: that the text is corrupt.
msgctxt "an5.194:3.3"
msgid "yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—"
msgstr ""
"whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing "
"stories—"

msgctxt "an5.194:3.4"
msgid "tato tato na aññesaṃ puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇappavādānaṃ piheti."
msgstr ""
"then you’re not attracted to the doctrines of the various ascetics and "
"brahmins."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso jighacchādubbalyapareto madhupiṇḍikaṃ adhigaccheyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person who was weak with hunger was to obtain a honey-cake."

msgctxt "an5.194:4.2"
msgid "So yato yato sāyetha, labhateva sādurasaṃ asecanakaṃ;"
msgstr "Wherever they taste it, they would enjoy a sweet, delicious flavor."

msgctxt "an5.194:4.3"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—"
msgstr "In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.194:4.4"
msgid "yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—"
msgstr ""
"whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing "
"stories—"

msgctxt "an5.194:4.5"
msgid "tato tato labhateva attamanataṃ, labhati cetaso pasādaṃ."
msgstr "then you get a sense of uplift, a confidence of the heart."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.238"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso candanaghaṭikaṃ adhigaccheyya—"
msgstr "Suppose a person were to obtain a piece of sandalwood,"

msgctxt "an5.194:5.2"
msgid "haricandanassa vā lohitacandanassa vā."
msgstr "whether yellow or red."

msgctxt "an5.194:5.3"
msgid "So yato yato ghāyetha—"
msgstr "Wherever they smelled it—"

msgctxt "an5.194:5.4"
msgid "yadi mūlato, yadi majjhato, yadi aggato—"
msgstr "whether at the root, the middle, or the top—"

#. VAR: adhigacchateva → adhigacchetheva (?)
msgctxt "an5.194:5.5"
msgid "adhigacchateva surabhigandhaṃ asecanakaṃ;"
msgstr "they’d enjoy a delicious fragrance."

msgctxt "an5.194:5.6"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—"
msgstr "In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.194:5.7"
msgid "yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—"
msgstr ""
"whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing "
"stories—"

msgctxt "an5.194:5.8"
msgid "tato tato adhigacchati pāmojjaṃ adhigacchati somanassaṃ."
msgstr "then you become filled with joy and happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno."
msgstr "Suppose there was a person who was sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "an5.194:6.2"
msgid "Tassa kusalo bhisakko ṭhānaso ābādhaṃ nīhareyya;"
msgstr "A good doctor would cure them on the spot."

msgctxt "an5.194:6.3"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—"
msgstr "In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.194:6.4"
msgid "yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—"
msgstr ""
"whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing "
"stories—"

msgctxt "an5.194:6.5"
msgid "tato tato sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"then you make an end of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā "
"ramaṇīyā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with "
"smooth banks, delightful."

msgctxt "an5.194:7.2"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched."

msgctxt "an5.194:7.3"
msgid ""
"So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhātvā ca pivitvā ca "
"sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhaṃ paṭippassambheyya."
msgstr ""
"They’d plunge into the lotus pond to bathe and drink. And all their stress, "
"weariness, and heat exhaustion would die down."

msgctxt "an5.194:7.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—"
msgstr "In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.194:7.5"
msgid "yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—"
msgstr ""
"whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing "
"stories—"

msgctxt "an5.194:7.6"
msgid "tato tato sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhā paṭippassambhantī”ti."
msgstr "then all your stress, weariness, and exhaustion die down.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:8.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā "
"dakkhiṇaṃ jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ pathaviyaṃ nihantvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā "
"tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, the brahmin Kāraṇapālī got up from his seat, arranged "
"his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms "
"toward the Buddha, and spoke these words of inspiration three times:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:9.1"
msgid "“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:10.1"
msgid "Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:11.1"
msgid "Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassāti."
msgstr ""
"Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.239"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.194:12.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni, abhikkantaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni."
msgstr "Excellent, Master Piṅgiyānī! Excellent!"

#. VAR: nikkujjitaṃ → nikujjitaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.194:12.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho piṅgiyāni, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: "
"‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā piṅgiyāninā anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Piṅgiyānī has made the teaching clear in "
"many ways."

msgctxt "an5.194:12.3"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca "
"bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an5.194:12.4"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī dhāretu, ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Piṅgiyānī remember me as a lay follower who "
"has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.194:12.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
